CINEMATIC_ATTACK_WHEN_POSSIBLE.label: No Dodging
CINEMATIC_ATTACK_WHEN_POSSIBLE.description: Use your fast attacks as quick as possible until you can unleash your charge attack

QUICK_ATTACK_ONLY.label: Only Fast Moves
QUICK_ATTACK_ONLY.description: Use your fast moves as quick as possible!

DODGE_SPECIALS2.label: Dodge Specials
DODGE_SPECIALS2.description: Use fast attacks until you can dodge their special, then use your charge attack.

DODGE_SPECIALS.label: Dodge Specials PRO
DODGE_SPECIALS.description: Use fast and charge moves as soon as you can, but dodge their charge attack!

DODGE_ALL2.label: Dodge All
DODGE_ALL2.description: Use fast attacks and dodge their moves until you can dodge their charge attack, then use your charge attack!

DODGE_ALL.label: Dodge All PRO
DODGE_ALL.description: Use fast attacks and charge attacks in between dodging all their moves!

DODGE_WEAVE_CAUTIOUS.label: Dodge All Weave
DODGE_WEAVE_CAUTIOUS.description: This uses an attack pattern strategy that assumes that the worst case 1.5s delay between attacks could happen every time. This strategy should be reproducible by a human.

undefined.label: Unknown
undefined.description: This should not occur. Please let us know this happened!

DODGE_100.label: Perfect Dodging
DODGE_100.description: Tries to dodge 100% of the time. This dodge strategy will almost never miss a dodge. You may still get hit in certain unavoidable situations such as when using a special move

DODGE_REACTION_TIME.label: Realistic Dodging
DODGE_REACTION_TIME.description: Attempts to simulate a realistic human dodger. Dodges vary from 50% success rate for a fast 1 second move to 90% success rate for a slow 3.5s move. In addition, if the attacker is using either super effective or not effective attacks, there is an additional 25% penalty to dodging, dropping the success rate to 37.5% to 67.5%. Finally a small bonus for faster attacker moves is added based on how much faster the move is than the dodge flash.

DODGE_REACTION_TIME2.label: Realistic Dodging Pro
DODGE_REACTION_TIME2.description: Attempts to simulate a realistic experienced human dodger. Dodges vary from 70% success rate for a fast 1 second move to 90% success rate for a slow 3.5s move. In addition, if the attacker is using either super effective or not effective attacks, there is an additional 10% penalty to dodging, dropping the success rate to 63.0% to 81.0%. Finally a small bonus for faster attack moves is added based on how much faster the move is than the dodge flash.

DODGE_25.label: 25% Dodging
DODGE_25.description: Chooses to dodge 25% of the time

DODGE_50.label: 50% Dodging
DODGE_50.description: Chooses to dodge 50% of the time

DODGE_75.label: 75% Dodging
DODGE_75.description: Chooses to dodge 75% of the time

DODGE_90.label: 90% Dodging
DODGE_90.description: Chooses to dodge 90% of the time

DUAL_MOVE.label: All Dual Charge Moves
DUAL_MOVE.description: All Pokemon use the best charge move combinations. Up to 30 movesets are returned.

SINGLE_MOVE.label: All Single Charge Moves
SINGLE_MOVE.description: All Pokemon use the best charge moves without learning a second move. Up to 12 movesets are returned.

DUAL_MOVE_3.label: Dual Charge Moves - Best 3
DUAL_MOVE_3.description: All Pokemon use the best charge move combinations. Up to 3 movesets are considered

SINGLE_MOVE_3.label: Single Charge Move - Best 3
SINGLE_MOVE_3.description: All Pokemon use the best charge moves without learning a second move. Up to 3 movesets are considered

DUAL_MOVE_1.label: Best Dual Charge Moves
DUAL_MOVE_1.description: All Pokemon use the best charge move combinations. Only the best moveset is considered

SINGLE_MOVE_1.label: Best Single Charge Move
SINGLE_MOVE_1.description: All Pokemon use the best charge moves without learning a second move. Only the best moveset is considered

SHIELD_RANDOM.label: Randomly Shield
SHIELD_RANDOM.description: Shields once 33% of the time and twice 17% of the time

SHIELD_1.label: Shield Once
SHIELD_1.description: Shields the first special move it can

SHIELD_2.label: Shield Twice
SHIELD_2.description: Shields the first two special moves it can

DEFENSE.label: Expected Defender
DEFENSE.description: Statistically valid expected result. Attacks come every 2 seconds and special attacks are always 1 attack late.

DEFENSE_LUCKY.label: Lucky Defender
DEFENSE_LUCKY.description: About as bad as it can get. Attacks come every 1.95s and special attacks are as early as possible

DEFENSE_RANDOM.label: Random
DEFENSE_RANDOM.description: Full random simulation! Attacks come between 1.5 and 2.5s apart. Special attacks are used 50% of the time if the defender has enough energy

DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_FAST.label: Monte Carlo - Bronze
DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_FAST.description: A more accurate result. 10 random simulations are run and averaged together to make one overall result. The median result based on overall rating is used for combat logs as an example. Most useful in combination with non-perfect dodge strategies.

DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_MID.label: Monte Carlo - Silver
DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_MID.description: A highly accurate result. 50 random simulations are run and averaged together to make one overall result. The median result based on overall rating is used for combat logs as an example. Most useful in combination with non-perfect dodge strategies.

DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC.label: Monte Carlo - Gold
DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC.description: The most accurate result. 200 random simulations are run and averaged together to make one overall result. The median result based on overall rating is used for combat logs as an example. Most useful in combination with non-perfect dodge strategies.

DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_EX.label: Monte Carlo - Platinum
DEFENSE_RANDOM_MC_EX.description: A special benefit for Fanatics and Champions. An excessively accurate result. 500 random simulations are run and combined together to make one overall result based on your aggregation choice. Most useful when looking at percentiles

DEFENSE_PATTERN.label: Defense Pattern - RNG
DEFENSE_PATTERN.description: An extremely predictable random number generator is used for this single simulation. This is used internally by Pokebattler for optimizing Monte Carlo simulations with random dodging

DEFENSE_PATTERN2.label: Defense Pattern
DEFENSE_PATTERN2.description: A pattern of delays and attacks is used for this single simulation. This is used internally by Pokebattler for optimizing Monte-Carlo simulations without dodging

POWER.label: $t(common:properties.power)
POWER.description: The percent of opponents health removed within the time limit

TIME.label: $t(common:properties.time)
TIME.description: Time to win assuming infinite number of Pokemon

POTIONS.description: 1 point for each potion and 5 points for each revive

ESTIMATOR.label: $t(common:properties.estimator)
ESTIMATOR.description: Approximate number of players required to win

PARTLY_CLOUDY.description: 20% bonus to Normal and Rock attacks

OVERCAST.label: Cloudy
OVERCAST.description: 20% bonus to Fairy, Fighting and Poison attacks

WINDY.label: Windy
WINDY.description: 20% bonus to Dragon, Flying and Psychic attacks

SNOW.label: Snow
SNOW.description: 20% bonus to Ice and Steel attacks

FOG.label: Fog
FOG.description: 20% bonus to Dark and Ghost attacks

AVERAGE.label: Average
AVERAGE.description: Average the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together. Note: The combat log and detailed damage reports are based on the median

MEDIAN.label: Expected - 50%
MEDIAN.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 50th percentile.

PERCENTILE_99.label: Extremely lucky - 99%
PERCENTILE_99.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 99th percentile.

PERCENTILE_95.label: Very lucky - 95%
PERCENTILE_95.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 95th percentile.

PERCENTILE_75.label: Lucky - 75%
PERCENTILE_75.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 75th percentile.

PERCENTILE_25.label: Unlucky - 25%
PERCENTILE_25.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 25th percentile.

PERCENTILE_5.label: Very Unlucky - 5%
PERCENTILE_5.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 5th percentile.

PERCENTILE_1.label: Extremely unlucky - 1%
PERCENTILE_1.description: Order the results of the Monte Carlo simulations together by Overall Rating and return the 1st percentile.

FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_0.label: Not Friends
FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_0.description: If you are not friends with anyone else in the raid, you get no bonus to attack. You can only trade regular Pokemon both players already own.

FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_1.label: Good Friends
FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_1.description: The maximum friend level you have with anyone at the raid. Good Friends get a 3% bonus to attack and can trade non-mythical Pokemon.

FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_2.label: Great Friends
FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_2.description: The maximum friend level you have with anyone at the raid. Great Friends get a 5% bonus to attack, 1 extra bonus ball in raids. They can trade non-mythical Pokemon with a 20% stardust discount.

FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_3.label: Ultra Friends
FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_3.description: The maximum friend level you have with anyone at the raid. Ultra Friends get a 7% bonus to attack, 2 extra bonus balls in raids. They can trade non-mythical Pokemon with a 92% stardust discount.

FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_4.label: Best Friends
FRIENDSHIP_LEVEL_4.description: The maximum friend level you have with anyone at the raid. Best Friends get a 10% bonus to attack and 4 extra bonus balls in raids. They can trade non-mythical Pokemon with a 96% stardust discount.
